## TDD â€” agent roles

Use TDD when adding behaviour with clear acceptance criteria. Delegate to **project subagents** in [`.cursor/agents/`](.cursor/agents/) or ask the user to invoke them by name (`tdd-red`, `tdd-green`, â€¦).

| Phase | Subagent | Goal | Allowed | Forbidden |
|-------|----------|------|---------|-----------|
| **Red** | `tdd-red` | Failing test proving missing/wrong behaviour | New/updated test in correct module; domain-named methods; minimal test code | Production `src/main` changes (except test fixtures) |
| **Green** | `tdd-green` | Minimal production code to pass Red test | Smallest `src/main` diff; reuse existing abstractions | New tests; refactors; scope beyond failing test |
| **Refactor** | `tdd-refactor` | Improve design with tests green | Rename, extract, dedupe, OOP cleanup per [stomp4j-oop-design.mdc](stomp4j-oop-design.mdc) | Behaviour change; new tests unless splitting one scenario |

**Cycle:** Red â†’ run test (must fail) â†’ Green â†’ run test (must pass) â†’ Refactor â†’ run module tests â†’ repeat.

**Parent agent:** delegate to `tdd-red` when user asks for TDD or new feature; chain `tdd-green` then `tdd-refactor` unless user stops at Green. Use `readonly: true` when launching Red via Task.

